## Proposed changes

pick: #23320

Support alter colocate group's replica allocation.

SQL command: ALTER COLOCATE GROUP [database.]group SET ("replication_allocation" = "...").

title: [fix](planner)isnull predicate can't be safely constant folded in inlineview
body:
## Proposed changes
disable is null predicate constant fold rule for inline view
consider sql 
select c.* 
from ( 
     select a.*, b.x
     from test_insert a left join 
               (select 'some_const_str' x from test_insert) b on true 
      ) c 
where **c.x is null**;

when push “c.x is null” into c, after folding constant rule, it will get empty result. Because x is 'some_const_str' and "x is null" will be evaluated to false. This is wrong.
